column1: The interviews revealed that there are three principal ways in which a NAFTA will influence domestic producers of textiles and apparel : ( 1 ) in eliminating requirements to cut and finish material within the US ; ( 2 ) in creating surplus capacity through the opening of new facilities to service the Mexican market ; and ( 3 ) in attracting foreign producers to Canada and Mexico in order to gain access to the US market .
